    • putData

      public int putData(OutputStream os) throws IOException
      Description copied from class: Protein
      Writes this protein's raw data to the given output stream, and returns the number of bytes written, which should be equal to the value returned by Protein.dataLength(). This method does not return until all the raw data has been accepted by the stream, or an I/O error occurs, in which case an IOException (possibly thrown by the given output stream) is thrown.
